text: Maryevka () is a rural locality (a village) in Kazadayevsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 56 as of 2010. There are 11 streets. == Geography == It is located 11 km from Sterlitamak, 5 km from Novoye Baryatino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Maryevka, Sterlitamaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
